      • serializeConstant

        protected void serializeConstant(int parameterIndex,
                                 java.lang.String constantLabel)
        Description copied from class: SerializerBase
        Serialize the constant as parameter to the query. The default implementation writes the label name for the constants. Some dialects may replace this by indexed based or positional parameterization. Dialects may also use this to prefix the parameter with for example ":" or "?".
        Overrides:
        serializeConstant in class SerializerBase<SQLSerializer>
        Parameters:
        parameterIndex - index at which this constant occurs in SerializerBase.getConstants()
        constantLabel - label under which this constant occurs in SerializerBase.getConstantToLabel()
